From: makvitaly
Date: 2026-05-15
Subject: feat: add PATCH /database/{db}/row/{row_id} for id-stable row upsert

AppFlowy-IO/AppFlowy-Cloud PR #1620

Adds a PATCH endpoint that upserts a database row by a client-provided
row_id from the URL path, preserving cells not sent in the body.

The PUT /row endpoint already implements the same business logic but
derives the row_id from SHA256(workspace_id + database_id + pre_hash),
which is unusable when the row_id is known but the pre_hash isn't
(e.g. rows created via the UI).

The PATCH endpoint takes the row_id directly from the URL, accepts the
same AddDatatabaseRow { cells, document } body as POST /row, and
delegates to the existing biz::collab::ops::upsert_database_row.

diff --git a/src/api/workspace.rs b/src/api/workspace.rs
index da06efa34..f113202fd 100644
--- a/src/api/workspace.rs
+++ b/src/api/workspace.rs
@@ -403,6 +403,10 @@ pub fn workspace_scope() -> Scope {
       web::resource("/{workspace_id}/database/{database_id}/row/detail")
         .route(web::get().to(list_database_row_details_handler)),
     )
+    .service(
